		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=7899"><span id=Scholar>Chimi</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br>18 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.50]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Chimi&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>So I decided upon reaching the 7th circle in my monk life that I was, in fact, going to max out all my combat skills so when I journyed forth into more group oriented levels, I wouldn't be stuck trying to do it then. At level 7 I had just maxed out my hand to hand( a whopping 40 for all unaccustomed to the max skill formula )and switched over to 1HB, using my mighty splintering club( semi light weight, low delay). To my dismay, I didn't max out 1hb till I was 4 1/2 bubbles into 7th, thus leaving me with one bubble of xp to max out my 2HB. So what I did was suicide myself, quite a few times, till I lost 2 bubs of xp ( getting killed by your bind point guards make for quite easy corpse retrieval ). I went back to my hunting grounds ( Nro in this case) and watched my 2HB skill slowly rise. But once again I rose more quickly than my skill, so whalla, back to the guards for another dirt nap. Eventually, i got the 2HB maxed out, and I was at balance with the universe.<br>Now, I know some of you out there are scratching your head wondering why I just didn't dump some training pts into my melee skills.....and I'll tell you, Monks get so many skills later on that I was saving them for those, feign death & Instill doubt to be specfic. <br>I am now of the 16th circle, all skills maxed (except for surefall, still have yet to find a good ledge to fall off for a mind-numbing 4 hours)<br>and can tear some Mob's up. If and when I bite the big one, I can still solo some blues whilst reteiving my corpse, as I have my HtH maxed, giving them my own brand of two-fisted justice.<br>I suppose the moral of the diatribe is to get those skills maxed out early and this is just the bizarre path I took to do it. Comprehension through Rigamortis I suppose.<br><br>-Chimi<br><br>/em Chimi ponders over his many deaths, then kicks Sgt. Slate in the beanbags one more time.<br><br>Sgt Slate slashes you for 60<br>Sgt Slate bashes you for 20<br>you are stunned<br>you are bleeding to death<br>pain and suffering<br>return to home point.<br><br></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >7 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
